Hurricane Floyd vented its fury on the Bahamas on Tuesday -- toppling trees and power lines, stripping roofs off homes and shoving a roiling sea into streets.
In Nassau, the capital, authorities lost telephone links throughout the vulnerable, low-lying archipelago -- including Eleuthera, San Salvador and Cat Island -- where winds reached 110 mph and damage was feared to be extensive.
Most residents were safely inside shelters; the island's popular Club Med resort had closed for the season.
